'''Cave of Zubialde''' is a [[Prehistoric cave art|prehistoric cave]] located in Zubialde, [[Gorbea]], Spain.<ref name=Ramírez>{{cite book |last=Alcina Franch |first=J. |last2=Bendala Galán |first2=M. |last3=Elvira |first3=M. A. |last4=García-Ormaechea |first4=C. |last5=Jiménez |first5=J. |last6=Olmos |first6=R. |last7=Padró |first7=J. |title=Historia del arte: El mundo antiguo |url=https://books.google.es/books?id=DL3pAAAAMAAJ |year=1997 |publisher=Alianza Editorial |volume=1 |isbn=9788420694818 |chapter=El arte de la Antigüedad en la hora actual |editor-last=Barandiarán |editor-first=Ignacio}}</ref> In 1990 it was subjected into an [[authentication]] by the use of [[electron microscopy]], [[chromatography]] and [[absolute dating]], so it was defined with a [[Black (color)|black]] and [[Red (colour)|red]] liquid [[painting]].<ref name=Ramírez/>

It was descovered in 1990 by Serafín Ruiz, a [[History]] student, and it was decorated by 20 [[animal figurine]]s and 49 [[hand symbol]]s.<ref>{{cite news |title=Zubialde, la falsa Altamira del País Vasco |url=http://www.abc.es/hemeroteca/historico-30-12-2005/abc/Sociedad/zubialde-la-falsa-altamira-del-pais-vasco_1013340603534.html |date=December 30, 2015 |access-date=April 12, 2018 |newspaper=[[ABC (Spain)|ABC]] |language=es}}</ref> It was the best prehistoric discovery of the decade and the most important of [[País Vasco]].<ref name=Góngora>{{cite news |last=Gónfora |first=F. |title=El estigma de Zubialde |url=http://www.elcorreo.com/vizcaya/20081120/sociedad/estigma-zubialde-20081120.html |year=2006 |access-date=April 12, 2018 |newspaper=[[El Correo]] |language=es}}</ref> It was dated in the [[Magdalenian]], [[Upper Paleolithic]] (13.000 y 10.000 BC).<ref name=Góngora/>

At the same year, [[Peter Ucko]], from the [[University of Southampton]], and [[Jill Cook]], from [[British Museum]] fathomed they were fake,<ref>{{cite newspaper |last=Ucko |first=Peter |author-link=Peter Ucko |last2=Cook |first2=Jill |author2-link=Jill Cook |newspaper=[[The European (newspaper)|The European]]}}</ref> and the [[Ertzaintza]] found out someone had painted the cave during 1990, and the main suspicious was Serafín Ruiz.<ref>{{cite news |last=Gorospe |first=Pedro |title=La Ertzaintza descubrió que alguien pintó en la cueva de Zubialde durante 1990 |url=https://elpais.com/diario/1992/08/14/cultura/713743205_850215.html |date=August 14, 1992 |access-date=April 12, 2018 |newspaper=[[El País]] |location=Vitoria |language=es}}</ref>

In 2008 was discovered another fraud in [[Iruña-Veleia]] similar with Zubialde.<ref>{{cite news |last=Azumendi |first=Eduardo |title=El caso resucita el episodio de la cueva de Zubialde |url=https://elpais.com/diario/2008/11/21/paisvasco/1227300003_850215.html |date=November 21, 2008 |access-date=April 12, 2018 |newspaper=[[El País]] |location=Vitoria |language=es}}</ref>

