{{Infobox World's Fair | box_width = | class = Specialized | image = | image_width = | caption = | year = 1991 | name = EXPO Plovdiv 1991 | motto = Young inventors at the service of world peace | building = [[International Fair Plovdiv]] | area = | invent = | visitors = | organized = | cnt = | org = | biz = | country = [[Bulgaria]] | city = [[Plovdiv]] | venue = | coord = | cand = | award = | open = June 7 1991 | close = July 7 1991 | prevexpo = [[World Expo 88]] | prevcity = [[Brisbane]] | nextexpo = [[Genoa Expo '92]] | nextcity = [[Genoa]] | suppl = Universal | prevsuppl = [[Expo '70]] | prevsupcity = [[Osaka]] | nextsuppl = [[Seville Expo '92]] | nextsupcity = [[Seville]] | simuni = | simspe = | simhor = | simoth = | website = }} The '''International Exhibition in Plovdiv''' was an international exhibition that was held from June 7 to July 7 of 1991 in the city of [[Plovdiv]], [[Bulgaria]], under the theme of "The creative activity of young inventors at the service of a world peace." The exhibition was coordinated by the [[Bureau International des Expositions]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bie-paris.org/site/en/library-a-publications/document-library/doc_download/268-plovdiv-1991-french.html |accessdate=22 December 2011 |title=PLOVDIV 91 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120608044644/http://www.bie-paris.org/site/en/library-a-publications/document-library/doc_download/268-plovdiv-1991-french.html |archivedate=June 8, 2012 }}</ref>
==Organizers== The organizers of the exhibition were:
*The Ministry of Economy and Planning of Bulgaria *The Chamber of Commerce and Industry of Bulgaria *The Republican Council of scientific and technical creativity of the youth of Bulgaria *International Foundation "Ludmila Jivkova" *The Institute of inventions and rationalizations.
The exhibition was organized with the cooperation of the [[World Intellectual Property Organization]], a specialized agency of the [[United Nations]].
