'''Frantz Vitko''' ({{lang-ru|Ф.П. Витко}}) was the president of the [[Federation of Trade Unions of Belarus]] (FPB) 2001-2002.<ref>[http://www.fpb.by/ru/menu_left/about Федерация профсоюзов Беларуси - О Федерации] {{webarchive |url=https://www.webcitation.org/5v9h2tPGL?url=http://www.fpb.by/ru/menu_left/about |date=December 22, 2010 }}</ref> Vitko, who had voiced criticism against the government, was persuaded to resign, and was replaced by [[Leonid Kozik]].<ref>[[ICFTU|Fria Fackföreningsinternationalen]]. ''Kränkningar av fackliga rättigheter / FFI''. [[Stockholm]]: LO-TCO biståndsnämnd, 2003. p. 264</ref>

