The '''Hereditary Quartermaster General of the Sacred Apostolic Palace''' (''Foriere Maggiore'') was one of the [[ceremonial]] offices within the [[Roman curia]], before the reform of the [[Pontifical Household]] in 1968.<ref>[http://www.serlupi.it/Corte_Pontificia.htm Corte_Pontificia]</ref> It was vested in the [[Marquesses  Sacchetti]], and is currently held by [[Marquess Giovanni Sacchetti]].  The former holder, Marquess Giovanni's father Marquess Giulio, was the highest [[layman]] in the [[Holy See|Vatican]] for 30 years, post the reforms of 1968,.<ref>[http://www.chivalricorders.org/vatican/pplcourt.htm THE HEREDITARY OFFICERS OF THE PAPAL COURT] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070313165610/http://www.chivalricorders.org/vatican/pplcourt.htm |date=2007-03-13 }}</ref><ref>[http://archive.catholicherald.co.uk/article/20th-april-1951/1/fifth-royal-visit-to-the-vatican FIFTH ROYAL VISIT TO THE VATICAN]</ref>  He died in 2010.

