'''Yusuf ibn al-Hasan''' (c. 1607-c. 1640), christened '''Dom Jerónimo Chingulia''', was ruler of [[Mombasa]] from 1614 to 1632.

After his father's assassination in 1614, he was sent to [[Goa]] to be educated, and was crowned Sultan in 1626.<ref name="EncycAfrica">{{cite book|last=Freeman-Grenville|first=GSP|title=New Encyclopedia of Africa|isbn=0-684-31455-X|pages=378–79|year=2008|publisher=Gale}}</ref> In August 1631, he renounced [[Christianity]], massacred the [[Portugal|Portuguese]] garrison and ordered all people in the city to convert to Islam.  In May 1632, he fled the city and turned to piracy.<ref name="MombasaCity">{{cite web|title=Brief History of Fort Jesus|url=http://www.mombasa-city.com/history_of_Fort_jesus.htm|website=www.mombasa-city.com|accessdate=20 February 2018}}</ref>

